Reploduce marginal-effect graph directly using mcmc samples

fm <- formula(fish_num ~ weather + temperature)
mat <- model.matrix(fm, df)

## factors and numerics in original data
weathersunny_unique <- mat[, "weathersunny"] %>% unique  # used in strata
temperature_unique <- mat[, "temperature"] %>% unique %>% unique  # x axis variable

## reproduce predected values using real explanatory variables
dup_mcmc <- function(mcmc, n) {
    apply(matrix(mcmc, nrow = 1), MARGIN = 2, FUN = function(x) rep(x, n))
}

## predict values using simulated variables
pred_lambdas <- lapply(weathersunny_unique, function(x) {
    dup_mcmc(mcmc_Intercept, length(temperature_unique)) + temperature_unique %*% 
        t(mcmc_temperature) + rep(x, length(temperature_unique)) %*% t(mcmc_weathersunny)
})

qts_pred_lambda <- lapply(pred_lambdas, function(X) {
    mx <- apply(X, MARGIN = 1, FUN = function(x) c(mean(x), quantile(x, probs = c(0.025, 
        0.1, 0.5, 0.9, 0.975)))) %>% t
    colnames(mx) <- c("mean", "p2.5", "p10", "p50", "p90", "p97.5")
    mx
}) %>% setNames(nm = c("cloudy", "sunny"))

df_qts_pred_lambda <- lapply(names(qts_pred_lambda), function(name) {
    qts_pred_lambda[[name]] %>% data.frame(check.names = F) %>% add_column(weather = name, 
        .before = T)
}) %>% bind_rows()

data.frame(temperature = temperature_unique, df_qts_pred_lambda, check.names = F) %>% 
    ggplot() + geom_line(aes(x = temperature, y = exp(mean), color = weather)) + 
    geom_ribbon(aes(x = temperature, ymin = exp(p2.5), ymax = exp(p97.5), fill = weather), 
        alpha = 0.4) + theme_bw(base_size = 14, base_rect_size = 0, base_line_size = 1) + 
    scale_fill_nejm() + scale_color_nejm() + geom_point(data = df, mapping = aes(x = temperature, 
    y = fish_num, color = weather, shape = weather), size = 2) + ylab("fish_num")

eff_pre <- marginal_effects(glm_pois_brms, method = "predict", effects = "temperature:weather", 
    probs = c(0.005, 0.995))
plot(eff_pre, points = T)[[1]] + theme_ipsum(base_size = 13) + scale_color_lancet() + 
    scale_fill_lancet() + theme(axis.title.x = element_text(size = 13), axis.title.y = element_text(size = 13), 
    legend.title = element_text(size = 13), legend.text = element_text(size = 12), 
    legend.position = c(0.04, 0.96), legend.justification = c(0, 1), legend.background = element_rect(color = "gray70"))

pred_mat <- expand.grid(weather = df$weather %>% unique, temperature = seq(0, 
    30, 0.5)) %>% mutate(weathersunny = ifelse(weather == "sunny", 1, 0))

pred_bx <- dup_mcmc(mcmc_Intercept, nrow(pred_mat)) + pred_mat$temperature %*% 
    t(mcmc_temperature) + pred_mat$weathersunny %*% t(mcmc_weathersunny)

pred_lambda <- exp(pred_bx)

set.seed(10)
generate_pois_pred <- function(lambdas, n_repeat) {
    res <- lapply(1:nrow(lambdas), function(i) {
        lambda_row <- lambdas[i, ]
        sapply(lambda_row, function(x) {
            rpois(n = n_repeat, lambda = x)
        }) %>% as.vector()
    })
    res
}
generated_values <- generate_pois_pred(pred_lambda, 10)

qts_gen_values <- lapply(generated_values, function(X) {
    qts <- c(mean(X), quantile(X, probs = c(0.005, 0.1, 0.5, 0.9, 0.995)))
    names(qts) <- c("mean", "p0.5", "p10", "p50", "p90", "p99.5")
    qts
}) %>% do.call(rbind, .) %>% data.frame(check.names = F)

df_qts_gen_values <- bind_cols(pred_mat, qts_gen_values)

manual_colors <- c("#69B3A2", "#404080")
df_qts_gen_values %>% ggplot() + geom_line(mapping = aes(x = temperature, y = p50, 
    color = weather), size = 1) + geom_point(data = df, mapping = aes(x = temperature, 
    y = fish_num, color = weather, shape = weather), size = 2) + geom_ribbon(mapping = aes(x = temperature, 
    ymin = p0.5, ymax = p99.5, fill = weather), alpha = 0.3) + theme_bw(base_size = 14, 
    base_rect_size = 0, base_line_size = 1) + scale_color_aaas() + scale_fill_aaas() + 
    ylab("number of fish") + ylim(c(0, 13)) + theme(legend.position = c(0.045, 
    0.99), legend.justification = c(0, 1), legend.background = element_rect(size = 1, 
    color = "gray80"))

poisson_formula <- formula(fish_num ~ temperature + weather)
data_mat <- model.matrix(poisson_formula, data = df)

stan_pois <- stan(file = "fish_poisson.stan", data = list(N = nrow(df), y = df$fish_num, 
    weathersunny = data_mat[, 3], temperature = df$temperature), chains = 4, 
    iter = 2000, thin = 1, warmup = 1000)

stan_result <- rstan::extract(stan_pois, permuted = F)
param_names <- dimnames(stan_result)$parameters

list_qts_stan <- lapply(param_names[1:length(param_names) - 1], function(name) {
    c(mean(stan_result[, , name]), quantile(stan_result[, , name], probs = c(0.025, 
        0.1, 0.5, 0.9, 0.975))) %>% setNames(nm = c("mean", "p2.5", "p10", "p50", 
        "p90", "97.5"))
}) %>% do.call(bind_rows, .) %>% add_column(params = param_names[1:length(param_names) - 
    1], .before = T)
